Sime Darby Says in Talks to Buy Distribution Assets of Bucyrus

-- B y   R a n j e e t h a   P a k i a m
-- 
2011-09-19T04:02:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/sime-darby-says-in-talks-to-buy-distribution-assets-of-bucyrus.html
Sime Darby Bhd. (SIME)  is in talks with
Caterpillar Inc. to buy some distribution assets of Bucyrus
International Inc., said Scott William Cameron, the executive
vice president of Sime’s industrial division.  Malaysia’s Sime may announce the deal by the end of the
year, he told reporters in Puchong, outside  Kuala Lumpur , today.  Caterpillar, the world’s largest maker of construction and
mining equipment, closed its $8.8 billion purchase of
Bucyrus on July 8 and said it planned to sell distribution
assets to dealers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ranjeetha Pakiam in Kuala Lumpur at 
 rpakiam@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chan Tien Hin at 
 thchan@bloomberg.net  